      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CONTRADICTION (8) made light work of a wide draw last time with a slick early sectional but gathered in and had to settle for the minors, finishing third (25.33) at Ballarat over 450m. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card last start despite being beaten. Sure to be about the mark. BONNIE BLITZ (1) is a talented type and proved too classy last time to win by one length at Horsham in a handy 23.42 beating Doongalla Jessie. Comes through a solid form race last start. Has hit winning form and can go on with it. IDYLLIC JAMES (3) is a capable type and proved too classy last time to win by 1.5 lengths at Warragul in a handy 22.53 beating Mr. Kia Ora. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card in scoring last start. Has hit winning form and can go on with it. PAW ELODEE (2) can play a role in the finish without surprising.",
